oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.oaext.osn.publicutil.converter.lookup
Class OsnAttributeLookupValueConverter

java.lang.Object
  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.oaext.osn.publicutil.converter.OsnFieldValueConverter
      oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.oaext.osn.publicutil.converter.lookup.OsnAttributeLookupValueConverter

public class OsnAttributeLookupValueConverter
extends OsnFieldValueConverter

A converter which looks up another value from the Row contained in the context using the displayAttributeName provided. If the Row does not have an attribute with the name set in displayAttributeName then an OsnConversionException will be thrown.

See OsnFieldValueConverter javadoc for more information on how to consume converters and the other override options.

convert

protected java.lang.Object convert(java.lang.Object initialValue,
                                   OsnConversionContext context)
                            throws OsnConversionException
The implementation of the conversion routine. If an issue occurs during the conversion meaning that the conversion cannot succeed then a OsnConversionException should be thrown. Looks up the attribute value on the row named by the displayAttributeName property and returns it.

Specified by:
convert in class OsnFieldValueConverter
Parameters:
initialValue - the value to convert.
context - additional data that is useful during the conversion.
Returns:
the looked up value.
Throws:
OsnConversionException - thrown if initialValue == null, there is an issue with the context or the display attribute name does not exist on the row.
